WEBVTT

00:00:04.240 --> 00:00:06.270
I did knock, for what it's worth.

00:00:06.270 --> 00:00:08.020
How did you find this place?

00:00:08.020 --> 00:00:10.540
I asked Hashida-san.

00:00:10.540 --> 00:00:12.430
He called it a "laboratory,"

00:00:12.430 --> 00:00:14.470
so I was expecting something
more than this...

00:00:14.470 --> 00:00:16.390
Daru, did you betray me?

00:00:17.700 --> 00:00:20.580
You were deceived by this
three-dimensional woman's wiles...

00:00:20.580 --> 00:00:24.530
I'll never forgive you! Ever!

00:00:24.530 --> 00:00:25.350
You... You...

00:00:25.350 --> 00:00:27.120
Bitch!

00:00:27.120 --> 00:00:29.280
Can you do anything about him?

00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:31.470
Just think of him as confused by events.

00:00:31.470 --> 00:00:33.820
This is an emergency.

00:00:33.820 --> 00:00:37.480
The Organization finally
sent an agent to the lab!

00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:38.360
What?

00:00:38.360 --> 00:00:40.640
Then this, too, is the choice of Steins Gate?

00:00:40.640 --> 00:00:42.270
Steins Gate?

00:00:42.270 --> 00:00:44.150
Something Okarin made up.

00:00:44.150 --> 00:00:45.390
It doesn't really mean anything.

00:00:45.390 --> 00:00:47.180
I'm sure.

00:00:47.180 --> 00:00:49.430
He's mixing up his German and English.

00:00:50.450 --> 00:00:52.100
Take your shoes off!

00:00:52.580 --> 00:00:54.560
I'm sorry.

00:00:54.560 --> 00:00:56.430
I've been in America too long.

00:00:58.930 --> 00:01:00.770
Nice to meet you.

00:01:00.770 --> 00:01:02.060
I'm Makise Kurisu.

00:01:04.190 --> 00:01:05.940
You can't even shake hands?

00:01:05.940 --> 00:01:09.220
Japanese men don't know
how to do anything.

00:01:12.180 --> 00:01:13.350
You're freaking out too much.

00:01:15.130 --> 00:01:18.040
It's because I can feel murderous intent
seeping from your every pore.

00:01:18.040 --> 00:01:20.840
Is this what they call the "martial arts"?

00:01:23.350 --> 00:01:24.820
Where are you going?

00:01:24.820 --> 00:01:29.180
Honestly, I came here to see if your claim
that I was stabbed was real

00:01:29.180 --> 00:01:31.470
or just an excuse for sexual harassment.

00:01:31.470 --> 00:01:36.930
But this is more important.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:44.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:03:22.390 --> 00:03:24.210
There's no damage to the connecting area.

00:03:24.210 --> 00:03:25.600
It's not some kind of trick.

00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:29.220
She may attempt to set
some kind of explosive.

00:03:29.220 --> 00:03:30.890
Don't look away from her for a second.

00:03:30.890 --> 00:03:32.430
No, she won't.

00:03:32.430 --> 00:03:33.300
Got any tweezers?

00:03:33.300 --> 00:03:33.720
No!

00:03:33.720 --> 00:03:34.100
I see.

00:03:35.270 --> 00:03:37.470
It's mushy inside.

00:03:37.470 --> 00:03:38.670
It tastes...

00:03:39.070 --> 00:03:40.350
Nothing.

00:03:40.350 --> 00:03:40.990
Ew!

00:03:40.990 --> 00:03:42.320
You zombie!

00:03:42.320 --> 00:03:44.230
If you're hungry, say so.

00:03:44.230 --> 00:03:45.740
I'll give you a banana.

00:03:45.740 --> 00:03:46.920
I'm fine.

00:03:46.920 --> 00:03:49.720
Who'd eat a pervert's banana anyway?

00:03:49.720 --> 00:03:50.740
Pervert?

00:03:50.740 --> 00:03:53.780
You poked at me,
trying to touch me, out of nowhere.

00:03:53.780 --> 00:03:55.270
Miss Makise? Miss Makise?

00:03:55.270 --> 00:03:55.970
Yes?

00:03:55.970 --> 00:03:59.790
Can you say,
"Who'd eat a pervert's banana anyway?"

00:03:59.790 --> 00:04:01.590
once more, you think?

00:04:01.590 --> 00:04:03.500
If possible, with an upset expression.

00:04:03.500 --> 00:04:04.600
Upset.

00:04:04.600 --> 00:04:05.150
Yes.

00:04:06.570 --> 00:04:08.050
Why the blushing?

00:04:08.050 --> 00:04:09.890
Did you imagine something?

00:04:09.890 --> 00:04:12.230
Say it, girl genius.

00:04:12.230 --> 00:04:16.890
Let's hear what the genius thought!

00:04:17.970 --> 00:04:20.560
It looks like you're both perverts.

00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:21.390
Oh, my...

00:04:21.390 --> 00:04:22.220
It's not a compliment.

00:04:22.220 --> 00:04:25.680
I would say the person with the
perverted imagination is the pervert.

00:04:25.680 --> 00:04:27.350
You're a perverted girl genius!

00:04:27.350 --> 00:04:29.270
Who's a pervert?

00:04:29.270 --> 00:04:30.220
Okay...

00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:32.450
To be honest, we're at the point where

00:04:32.450 --> 00:04:35.180
I could sue you for sexual harassment
this minute, but I'll forget it for now.

00:04:35.180 --> 00:04:36.220
For now?

00:04:36.220 --> 00:04:38.420
So tell me the details.

00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:41.930
This banana has something to do
with that microwave, right?

00:04:41.930 --> 00:04:43.730
It's top-secret!

00:04:43.730 --> 00:04:46.570
Future Gadget #8, the Phone Microwave,

00:04:46.570 --> 00:04:48.930
is my lab's secret weapon.

00:04:50.470 --> 00:04:55.770
But Miss Makise might be able to explain
how this weird thing works.

00:04:55.770 --> 00:04:56.820
But...

00:04:56.820 --> 00:05:00.470
You need to understand, we'll never
figure this out on our own.

00:05:00.940 --> 00:05:04.500
But this is the Future Gadget Lab's...

00:05:08.420 --> 00:05:09.340
You!

00:05:09.340 --> 00:05:11.120
Christina, you said?

00:05:11.120 --> 00:05:12.470
No, I never said that.

00:05:12.470 --> 00:05:14.690
I'll tell you the secrets of the Phone Microwave,

00:05:14.690 --> 00:05:16.600
but on two conditions!

00:05:16.600 --> 00:05:22.820
One, you must become a
Future Gadget Lab member.

00:05:22.820 --> 00:05:26.440
You want me to join your lab?

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:31.930
But I'm returning to America in August...

00:05:31.930 --> 00:05:33.270
It can be just until then.

00:05:33.760 --> 00:05:34.950
And one more.

00:05:34.950 --> 00:05:35.850
There's more?

00:05:35.850 --> 00:05:39.680
Forget about any
sexual harassment I've done.

00:05:41.060 --> 00:05:42.050
That's it.

00:05:42.050 --> 00:05:43.580
Okarin, you're a small person.

00:05:43.580 --> 00:05:46.190
A very small person.

00:05:46.190 --> 00:05:48.740
And I love that. Love it!

00:05:48.740 --> 00:05:49.830
Shut up!

00:05:49.830 --> 00:05:50.890
Well?

00:05:50.890 --> 00:05:52.390
I think the conditions are very favorable...

00:05:52.390 --> 00:05:54.260
Favorable to you.

00:05:54.260 --> 00:05:55.330
Jeez...

00:05:55.330 --> 00:05:57.430
You're making my brain put out
too much noradrenaline.

00:05:57.430 --> 00:05:59.520
What will you do, Christina?

00:05:59.520 --> 00:06:01.560
There's no "-tina!"

00:06:01.560 --> 00:06:03.430
Sorry, "The Zombie."

00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:06.510
Say it right, Hououin Pervert-Kyouma!

00:06:06.510 --> 00:06:07.310
What?

00:06:07.310 --> 00:06:09.020
Pervert Girl Genius!

00:06:09.860 --> 00:06:12.330
Perverts glaring at each other... Win!

00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:13.900
Shut up, pervert!

00:06:13.900 --> 00:06:15.370
Oh, fine.

00:06:15.370 --> 00:06:16.610
All right.

00:06:16.610 --> 00:06:17.630
I accept.

00:06:17.630 --> 00:06:19.660
So no more "Pervert."

00:06:19.660 --> 00:06:21.910
I'll stop calling you one, too.

00:06:21.910 --> 00:06:23.160
Very well.

00:06:23.160 --> 00:06:26.850
Then from now on, you're Lab Member 004!

00:06:26.850 --> 00:06:29.400
Christina!

00:06:29.400 --> 00:06:30.600
No "-tina," either!

00:06:30.600 --> 00:06:34.680
Juicy Kara-age #1... Wow!

00:06:34.680 --> 00:06:36.500
I'm back!

00:06:34.680 --> 00:06:36.500
You think it's a teleporter?

00:06:36.500 --> 00:06:38.620
It's dangerous to jump to conclusions.

00:06:38.620 --> 00:06:40.320
Then what do you think it is?

00:06:40.320 --> 00:06:41.440
If nothing else,

00:06:41.440 --> 00:06:45.170
it didn't teleport the Juicy Kara-age
or the banana bunch.

00:06:42.460 --> 00:06:45.810
One, two, three, four...

00:06:45.810 --> 00:06:47.610
A guest?

00:06:49.180 --> 00:06:50.720
Hello there.

00:06:50.720 --> 00:06:52.510
I'm Makise Kurisu.

00:06:52.510 --> 00:06:54.790
I'm sorry to just show up, out of the blue.

00:06:54.790 --> 00:06:56.390
Shiina Mayuri.

00:06:56.390 --> 00:06:59.310
It looks like I'm a lab member now, too.

00:06:59.310 --> 00:07:01.210
A lab member?

00:07:01.210 --> 00:07:02.230
Yes...

00:07:02.230 --> 00:07:05.610
A girl lab member!

00:07:05.610 --> 00:07:08.250
Is it that rare?

00:07:08.250 --> 00:07:10.190
Yes! Yes! Yes!

00:07:10.190 --> 00:07:13.840
You're the first girl lab member
after Mayushii!

00:07:13.840 --> 00:07:14.640
I see.

00:07:15.180 --> 00:07:16.390
Nice to meet you.

00:07:16.390 --> 00:07:18.190
Yes, nice to meet you.

00:07:18.190 --> 00:07:19.140
What?

00:07:19.140 --> 00:07:20.410
What happened?

00:07:20.410 --> 00:07:22.210
There was some electrical release.

00:07:22.710 --> 00:07:25.050
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

00:07:25.050 --> 00:07:26.870
Give me the details.

00:07:26.870 --> 00:07:29.180
Um... Well...

00:07:29.180 --> 00:07:31.810
Some kind of lightning came
from the microwave.

00:07:31.810 --> 00:07:32.850
When?

00:07:32.850 --> 00:07:35.170
Yesterday, around noon.

00:07:35.170 --> 00:07:39.270
You saw the thing about
the satellite crash and ran out,

00:07:39.270 --> 00:07:41.600
and I connected my phone to it.

00:07:45.270 --> 00:07:47.830
Then, when I sent that message,

00:07:47.830 --> 00:07:51.220
your phone was hooked up to the
Phone Microwave?

00:07:51.220 --> 00:07:54.380
The one about Miss Makise being stabbed?

00:07:54.380 --> 00:07:56.000
That was a week ago, wasn't it?

00:07:56.000 --> 00:07:58.850
No, that was yesterday!

00:08:00.060 --> 00:08:02.200
Where is it? Where is it?

00:08:02.200 --> 00:08:03.480
Why isn't it here?!

00:08:03.480 --> 00:08:06.050
When this happened,
what was the microwave doing?

00:08:06.050 --> 00:08:08.010
I was doing a systems test...

00:08:08.010 --> 00:08:10.840
So I think it was during
the reverse spinning testing.

00:08:10.840 --> 00:08:12.680
We should try to recreate this.

00:08:12.680 --> 00:08:16.090
Mayuri, bring me the Juicy Kara-age #1!

00:08:16.090 --> 00:08:16.890
Okay!

00:08:16.890 --> 00:08:18.660
You want some, everyone?

00:08:18.660 --> 00:08:20.720
I can give each of you one.

00:08:20.720 --> 00:08:22.070
Do we need to put something in there?

00:08:22.070 --> 00:08:23.230
I want to see

00:08:23.230 --> 00:08:26.350
what happens to its contents
when it revolves backwards.

00:08:26.870 --> 00:08:27.430
Daru.

00:08:30.520 --> 00:08:33.370
Assistant, send a message to my phone.

00:08:33.370 --> 00:08:35.850
Since when am I your assistant?

00:08:35.850 --> 00:08:38.140
And I don't know your address.

00:08:38.140 --> 00:08:40.170
Useless assistant.

00:08:40.170 --> 00:08:42.020
Daru, your phone's fine.

00:08:42.020 --> 00:08:43.420
What should the subject be?

00:08:43.420 --> 00:08:44.390
Let me see.

00:08:44.390 --> 00:08:46.590
"Christina is a pervert."

00:08:46.590 --> 00:08:48.270
I told you that's off-limits.

00:08:48.270 --> 00:08:52.970
Then we'll split the difference
and go with "Okarin is a pervert"...

00:08:52.970 --> 00:08:53.510
What?

00:08:53.510 --> 00:08:55.190
Hashida-san, good job!

00:08:55.190 --> 00:08:57.060
Okay, sending.

00:08:58.210 --> 00:09:00.600
Now we wait for the message
to arrive at the phone...

00:09:00.600 --> 00:09:02.930
I bet it's ready now!

00:09:03.490 --> 00:09:04.430
Wait!

00:09:17.390 --> 00:09:18.890
Are you okay?

00:09:18.890 --> 00:09:20.220
Yeah...

00:09:21.860 --> 00:09:23.220
Gotta turn on the fan!

00:09:27.980 --> 00:09:29.650
What is this?

00:09:29.650 --> 00:09:31.640
The EM waves maybe?

00:09:31.640 --> 00:09:33.420
Don't be stupid.

00:09:33.420 --> 00:09:38.120
A microwave's EM waves
couldn't split a desk so quickly.

00:09:38.120 --> 00:09:40.060
They're all black!

00:09:40.060 --> 00:09:42.680
And I just bought them, too!

00:09:42.680 --> 00:09:44.530
What do we do about the hole in the floor?

00:09:44.530 --> 00:09:47.320
If Mr. Braun finds that,
we're in serious trouble.

00:09:53.100 --> 00:09:54.060
Well?

00:09:54.060 --> 00:09:54.680
It's here.

00:09:55.370 --> 00:09:59.020
7/24, 17:30.

00:09:59.460 --> 00:10:01.310
<i>It went back to the past...</i>

00:10:05.030 --> 00:10:06.220
Did you find something?

00:10:06.220 --> 00:10:08.580
Yes. It's all coming together!

00:10:08.580 --> 00:10:09.760
I can see it...

00:10:09.760 --> 00:10:12.510
The one answer this all points to!

00:10:12.510 --> 00:10:13.660
Really?

00:10:14.340 --> 00:10:17.790
The banana, split off from
the bunch, returned to it!

00:10:17.790 --> 00:10:19.930
The message traveled five days into the past.

00:10:19.930 --> 00:10:22.490
No way. You can't mean...

00:10:22.490 --> 00:10:23.560
That's right!

00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:26.020
The Phone Microwave
 is...

00:10:30.160 --> 00:10:32.430
...a time machine!

00:10:44.720 --> 00:10:47.740
Thirteen messages?

00:10:48.440 --> 00:10:50.310
The lightning...

00:10:51.070 --> 00:10:52.560
Oh, right.

00:10:52.560 --> 00:10:55.100
I dubbed her the "Shining Finger."

00:10:55.100 --> 00:10:58.100
But this many?

00:10:58.100 --> 00:10:59.600
"Message me now."

00:10:59.600 --> 00:11:01.420
"Are you asleep?"

00:11:01.420 --> 00:11:03.670
"How long are you going to sleep?"

00:11:03.670 --> 00:11:05.200
Daru?

00:11:08.100 --> 00:11:10.440
Wanna go for a walk?

00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:12.830
What's wrong?

00:11:12.830 --> 00:11:14.650
Damage is pretty bad.

00:11:14.650 --> 00:11:16.640
I worked all night,
with nothing to show for it.

00:11:16.640 --> 00:11:19.140
I regret trying.

00:11:19.140 --> 00:11:22.510
Why aren't they turning
into gel-banas anymore?

00:11:24.720 --> 00:11:26.110
Hell if I know.

00:11:26.110 --> 00:11:28.470
That was the only time
we were able to send a message.

00:11:28.470 --> 00:11:32.020
Shouldn't we call Miss Makise back?

00:11:32.020 --> 00:11:33.930
You know that's not happening.

00:11:34.020 --> 00:11:35.600
No way.

00:11:35.600 --> 00:11:37.460
A time machine?

00:11:40.430 --> 00:11:42.840
She never came back.

00:11:42.840 --> 00:11:44.750
What was that?

00:11:45.460 --> 00:11:46.940
What is this?

00:11:46.940 --> 00:11:49.210
The LHC.

00:11:50.080 --> 00:11:51.930
The Large Hadron Collider,

00:11:51.930 --> 00:11:54.220
SERN's particle accelerator.

00:11:54.220 --> 00:11:57.080
Makes you feel better, just looking at it...

00:12:00.660 --> 00:12:05.810
<i>SERN maintains an exclusive monopoly
on time machines.</i>

00:12:06.850 --> 00:12:09.520
John Titor...

00:12:09.520 --> 00:12:12.100
Oh, the one you were talking about.

00:12:12.100 --> 00:12:14.800
@channel can't get enough of the guy.

00:12:14.800 --> 00:12:16.520
What is SERN?

00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:21.600
Titor was saying that they finish
a time machine by 2034!

00:12:21.600 --> 00:12:23.180
I have no idea what you're talking about...

00:12:23.180 --> 00:12:24.470
Just tell me!

00:12:24.470 --> 00:12:25.440
What is SERN?

00:12:25.440 --> 00:12:27.390
Calm down.

00:12:27.390 --> 00:12:31.190
It's the acronym for the European Organization
in Nuclear Research and Particle Physics.

00:12:31.190 --> 00:12:33.490
Its HQ is just outside Geneva.

00:12:33.490 --> 00:12:37.290
Like the name suggests,
its main work is in particle physics.

00:12:37.290 --> 00:12:40.890
And it has some of the world's best facilities for it:

00:12:40.890 --> 00:12:42.520
The Low Energy Antiproton Ring.

00:12:42.520 --> 00:12:44.750
The Proton Synchrotron Booster.

00:12:44.750 --> 00:12:46.810
The Large Electron–Positron Collider...

00:12:46.810 --> 00:12:48.520
And the last boss,

00:12:48.520 --> 00:12:51.230
the world's biggest particle accelerator,

00:12:51.230 --> 00:12:54.030
Large Hadron Collider-tan!

00:12:55.750 --> 00:13:02.930
There were rumors that the LHC
could generate a mini-black hole.

00:13:05.190 --> 00:13:06.600
A black hole...

00:13:06.600 --> 00:13:07.590
Daru.

00:13:07.590 --> 00:13:08.310
'Sup?

00:13:09.040 --> 00:13:13.150
Didn't one proposed time travel method

00:13:13.150 --> 00:13:16.270
use a mini-black hole?

00:13:16.270 --> 00:13:18.580
Yeah, it did.

00:13:18.580 --> 00:13:21.390
But you heard Miss Makise's lecture, right?

00:13:21.390 --> 00:13:25.100
She said creating a
black hole was impossible.

00:13:25.100 --> 00:13:27.870
But if the LHC exists,

00:13:27.870 --> 00:13:29.580
then it's possible...

00:13:28.690 --> 00:13:29.580
It is!

00:13:29.580 --> 00:13:30.920
No, it isn't.

00:13:30.920 --> 00:13:32.810
SERN's publicly denied it.

00:13:32.810 --> 00:13:36.670
But they say that
where there's smoke, there's fire.

00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:37.700
It's me.

00:13:37.220 --> 00:13:40.180
No Cell Phones

00:13:38.570 --> 00:13:40.180
That's right. I know.

00:13:40.180 --> 00:13:42.470
El Psy Congroo.

00:13:42.470 --> 00:13:45.330
Who, exactly, are you fighting?

00:13:45.330 --> 00:13:48.710
There's only one thing for us to do now.

00:13:48.710 --> 00:13:50.350
Go see Feyris-tan!

00:13:50.350 --> 00:13:51.060
No!

00:13:51.060 --> 00:13:53.300
You're a super haker, right?

00:13:53.300 --> 00:13:55.110
You should smile knowingly!

00:13:55.110 --> 00:13:57.340
It's "hacker," not "haker," okay?

00:13:57.340 --> 00:13:58.570
You understand the rest?

00:13:58.570 --> 00:14:00.230
Not a bit.

00:14:02.030 --> 00:14:03.430
Hack into SERN.

00:14:05.080 --> 00:14:06.640
That's it.

00:14:06.640 --> 00:14:09.600
Okarin... This is a joke, right?

00:14:09.600 --> 00:14:11.680
You need to find out what
evil they're up to

00:14:11.680 --> 00:14:14.130
and get a hint about the time machine.

00:14:14.810 --> 00:14:18.830
Whether we make the Phone Microwave
into a real time machine

00:14:18.830 --> 00:14:22.910
or let it rest forever in the lab storeroom,
is up to your skills.

00:14:22.910 --> 00:14:24.730
Don't blame me for the outcome!

00:14:24.730 --> 00:14:26.390
Two orders of gyuudon.

00:14:26.390 --> 00:14:27.900
800 yen, total.

00:14:27.900 --> 00:14:29.600
Okarin!

00:14:32.360 --> 00:14:34.230
Slacking off again?

00:14:34.230 --> 00:14:37.500
Yeah, the shop's boring.

00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:38.870
Nothing to do.

00:14:38.870 --> 00:14:41.470
You're more of a bicycle shop now.

00:14:41.470 --> 00:14:45.890
Anyway, what are you doing
on the second floor?

00:14:45.890 --> 00:14:48.300
Future Gadget Lab, right?

00:14:48.300 --> 00:14:49.810
Where did you learn that name?

00:14:51.640 --> 00:14:52.560
Future Gadget Lab

00:14:53.170 --> 00:14:56.050
If you know that much, then fine.

00:14:56.050 --> 00:14:58.670
We're fighting against an organization

00:14:58.670 --> 00:15:01.190
that rules the world from the shadows.

00:15:01.190 --> 00:15:05.650
Just now, we're hacking into that organization.

00:15:06.290 --> 00:15:10.140
So, is SERN that organization?

00:15:10.140 --> 00:15:11.570
How did you know?

00:15:11.570 --> 00:15:12.650
I'm sorry.

00:15:12.650 --> 00:15:16.100
Actually, I overheard you guys.

00:15:16.100 --> 00:15:17.880
I said I was bored.

00:15:17.880 --> 00:15:18.730
So, accidentally...

00:15:18.730 --> 00:15:20.870
You were spying on us?

00:15:20.870 --> 00:15:23.070
I can hear you.

00:15:23.070 --> 00:15:24.910
But don't worry.

00:15:24.910 --> 00:15:26.980
I'm good at keeping my mouth shut.

00:15:29.450 --> 00:15:30.400
Again?

00:15:30.400 --> 00:15:32.660
What? A message that someone died?

00:15:32.660 --> 00:15:33.890
Someone died?

00:15:33.890 --> 00:15:36.840
N-No... I was just kidding.

00:15:36.840 --> 00:15:39.790
This girl's obsessed with some old PC

00:15:39.790 --> 00:15:41.920
called an IBN 5100.

00:15:41.920 --> 00:15:42.810
An IBN?

00:15:42.810 --> 00:15:44.140
You know it?

00:15:45.810 --> 00:15:47.640
Um... Yeah.

00:15:47.640 --> 00:15:49.800
You heard that, too?

00:15:49.800 --> 00:15:52.970
No, I saw it on the internet.

00:15:52.970 --> 00:15:55.450
You know, that guy who claimed
to be a time traveler?

00:15:55.450 --> 00:15:57.360
John Titor, was it?

00:15:57.360 --> 00:15:58.240
Titor?

00:15:58.240 --> 00:16:01.230
It was on @channel.

00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:06.980
The IBN 5100 was created before BASIC.

00:16:06.980 --> 00:16:10.390
So it can read IBN's proprietary
programming languages or something...

00:16:10.390 --> 00:16:11.130
Really?!

00:16:11.130 --> 00:16:11.930
Yeah.

00:16:12.370 --> 00:16:15.640
Come to think of it, the Titor
who appeared in 2000 also...

00:16:20.710 --> 00:16:26.800
You all seem to have fixed ideas
about the nature of time.

00:16:22.720 --> 00:16:24.950
031 Name: Nameless Prophet-san [sage]
John Titor took a dump, and now the universe is doomed...

00:16:26.850 --> 00:16:32.910
032 Name: Chestnut Rice and Kamehameha [sage]
This is getting more disappointing
None of this is really concrete
I realize you're doing your best to sound realistic, but you can't fool me.

00:16:27.410 --> 00:16:33.430
Time isn't a single line,
moving from past to future.

00:16:34.740 --> 00:16:40.150
Let's say I go back in time and
kill someone we'll call "A."

00:16:40.150 --> 00:16:44.580
This alters something called
the divergence number,

00:16:44.580 --> 00:16:49.300
and the world line moves to a world without A.

00:16:50.040 --> 00:16:54.580
When there's a world line move,
people's memories are altered.

00:16:54.580 --> 00:16:59.980
In other words, memories of the
world line where A existed are deleted,

00:16:59.980 --> 00:17:06.350
replaced with memories of a
world line where A doesn't exist.

00:17:06.350 --> 00:17:09.300
I'm more interested in how SERN,

00:17:08.810 --> 00:17:11.850
214 Name: Chestunut Rice and Kamehama [sage]
I'm more interested in how SERN,
a research organization, ends up as planetary ruler,
a question I've been asking for a while now.

00:17:09.300 --> 00:17:13.130
a research organization,
ends up as planetary ruler,

00:17:13.130 --> 00:17:15.350
a question I've been asking for a while now.

00:17:15.350 --> 00:17:18.770
Don't believe what SERN says.

00:17:15.810 --> 00:17:18.770
343 Name: Nameless Prophet [sage]
And this results in a dystopia?

00:17:18.770 --> 00:17:23.310
They've already succeeded in
creating a mini-black hole.

00:17:19.470 --> 00:17:23.310
357 Name: Nameless Prophet [sage]
What's a dystopia?

00:17:23.800 --> 00:17:27.360
It would be easiest to describe a dystopia
as the revival of communism,

00:17:27.360 --> 00:17:31.930
and the world's reversion to
18th-century living standards.

00:17:32.440 --> 00:17:38.300
By 2036, SERN holds most of
the world's science and technology.

00:17:37.540 --> 00:17:38.220
472 Name: Nameless Prophet [sage]
Guess what I had for dinner tomorrow!

00:17:38.220 --> 00:17:38.680
473 Name: [sage]
I want to know the future!

00:17:38.300 --> 00:17:43.610
And you need the IBN 5100
to change this future?

00:17:43.610 --> 00:17:44.810
That's correct.

00:17:45.570 --> 00:17:51.600
I need the IBN 5100's abilities
to stop their plans.

00:17:51.600 --> 00:17:56.560
The John Titor who appeared in 2000
said the same thing.

00:17:51.620 --> 00:17:56.560
558 Name: Hououin Kyouma [age]
The John Titor who appeared in 2000
said the same thing...

00:17:52.640 --> 00:17:56.560
559 Name: Nameless Prophet [sage]
Dude, just shut up already.

00:17:56.560 --> 00:17:59.540
The "me" who appeared ten years ago?

00:17:59.540 --> 00:18:05.010
As I said, I've unfortunately
never been to the year 2000.

00:18:05.010 --> 00:18:10.180
But it's possible you saw me
in a different world line.

00:18:10.180 --> 00:18:11.790
Interesting.

00:18:11.790 --> 00:18:14.750
I'd like to talk to you in detail.

00:18:15.520 --> 00:18:17.940
This is my address.

00:18:15.540 --> 00:18:18.930
In 2015, WW3 occurs.
In 2036, Earth is polluted by nuclear warfare.
I've time traveled from 2036 to get an IBN 5100.
The IBN 5100 has a hidden function.
Only a few IBN engineers know this.

00:18:17.940 --> 00:18:20.930
If you contact me, I'll answer.

00:18:26.100 --> 00:18:28.820
I've almost got it.

00:18:28.820 --> 00:18:35.410
If I can just get the SQL table list,
figuring out the password should be easy.

00:18:33.260 --> 00:18:34.610
Good morning!

00:18:35.930 --> 00:18:37.260
Mayuri?

00:18:37.260 --> 00:18:39.180
What brings you here so early?

00:18:39.180 --> 00:18:43.470
I heard you've been up two nights in a row,
so I brought snacks.

00:18:44.320 --> 00:18:45.890
Here you go.

00:18:46.680 --> 00:18:47.890
Canned oden!

00:18:47.890 --> 00:18:48.940
Great!

00:18:48.940 --> 00:18:50.430
Bring me another sometime, Mayuri.

00:18:50.430 --> 00:18:56.140
Mayushii doesn't have enough
pocket money to treat you too often.

00:18:56.140 --> 00:18:59.310
I need to buy my Rai-Net sausage, also!

00:18:59.310 --> 00:19:00.890
Upa again?

00:19:00.890 --> 00:19:04.020
So I want you to enjoy this!

00:19:04.020 --> 00:19:06.750
There's some for Daru-kun
and Kurisu-chan, too.

00:19:07.960 --> 00:19:09.860
That's not it!

00:19:09.860 --> 00:19:11.780
He's not listening at all.

00:19:11.780 --> 00:19:13.600
I told him to rest, though.

00:19:13.600 --> 00:19:18.140
His super haker's soul is burning bright!

00:19:18.140 --> 00:19:19.990
Don't say "haker"!

00:19:23.150 --> 00:19:26.620
But it's bad to nose around in
other people's secrets, isn't it?

00:19:26.620 --> 00:19:29.070
This is to reveal SERN's plots.

00:19:29.070 --> 00:19:30.560
Even so...

00:19:30.560 --> 00:19:35.770
I'm sure Kurisu-chan left
because she was mad.

00:19:35.770 --> 00:19:38.490
No, that had nothing to do with the hacking.

00:19:38.490 --> 00:19:40.190
My assistant ran off on her own.

00:19:40.190 --> 00:19:43.410
I wonder if she'll come back...

00:19:47.690 --> 00:19:48.680
Huh?

00:19:48.680 --> 00:19:49.780
What?

00:19:49.780 --> 00:19:51.880
I'll trade a satsuma for a beef strip.

00:19:52.490 --> 00:19:54.510
Then I'd rather have an uzura.

00:19:54.510 --> 00:19:55.480
No.

00:19:55.480 --> 00:19:58.140
I like uzura almost as much
as I like beef strips.

00:19:58.140 --> 00:20:00.840
Mayushii likes uzura, too!

00:20:00.840 --> 00:20:02.640
Then I'll give you a chikuwa instead.

00:20:03.530 --> 00:20:05.580
I guess I like chikuwa more than satsuma.

00:20:05.580 --> 00:20:07.310
Okay, then negotiations are concluded.

00:20:07.310 --> 00:20:09.870
Then here's my beef strip...

00:20:10.340 --> 00:20:11.390
I ate it already.

00:20:12.110 --> 00:20:13.140
When did you...

00:20:15.650 --> 00:20:17.500
It was good.

00:20:20.460 --> 00:20:23.520
I got it!

00:20:23.860 --> 00:20:26.200
I got it! I got it! I got it!
I got it! I got it!

00:20:26.200 --> 00:20:29.770
Now give up, and show me everything.

00:20:29.980 --> 00:20:31.160
I got it!

00:20:31.160 --> 00:20:32.920
ID get!

00:20:31.800 --> 00:20:32.920
You did it?

00:20:32.920 --> 00:20:34.940
Mission complete!

00:20:35.400 --> 00:20:36.740
Wow!

00:20:36.740 --> 00:20:38.660
I don't understand, but wow.

00:20:38.660 --> 00:20:40.850
Well, the hacking's done,

00:20:40.850 --> 00:20:44.640
but there are limits to what I can see,
without being an admin.

00:20:44.640 --> 00:20:47.020
It's like I can only see the boobs.

00:20:47.020 --> 00:20:48.610
You're so naughty, Daru-kun.

00:20:48.610 --> 00:20:49.840
What did you get?

00:20:49.840 --> 00:20:53.280
So far, just some e-mail.

00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:54.550
English?

00:20:54.550 --> 00:20:56.270
Let's get Dr. Excite in here.

00:20:56.270 --> 00:20:59.050
No way, that's a pain.

00:20:59.050 --> 00:21:01.550
It says "Hi Paul!"

00:21:01.550 --> 00:21:03.200
We don't need your acting.

00:21:03.200 --> 00:21:04.410
No?

00:21:05.390 --> 00:21:08.200
"The LHC is working well.

00:21:08.200 --> 00:21:10.880
It's as fickle as a cat,
but for the past month,

00:21:10.880 --> 00:21:13.540
it's been working surprisingly well."

00:21:13.540 --> 00:21:14.760
What's he talking about?

00:21:15.950 --> 00:21:19.430
Anyway, does anything here
mention a time machine?

00:21:19.430 --> 00:21:22.880
The phrase "time machine" doesn't show up,

00:21:22.880 --> 00:21:27.830
but in the last month, the word "Z-program"
has been used over one hundred times.

00:21:27.830 --> 00:21:28.780
Let's see...

00:21:28.780 --> 00:21:33.190
"Z-Program Experiment Report 137."

00:21:34.180 --> 00:21:39.220
"The mini-black hole mission
has already been established,

00:21:39.220 --> 00:21:41.140
so I'll skip that report."

00:21:42.050 --> 00:21:43.770
Mini-black hole...

00:21:43.770 --> 00:21:44.950
Looks right.

00:21:44.950 --> 00:21:48.430
They publicly said that those
experiments were a failure.

00:21:48.430 --> 00:21:49.770
What else does it say?

00:21:49.770 --> 00:21:51.430
"Experiment result..."

00:21:54.770 --> 00:21:56.880
"Human is dead,

00:21:56.880 --> 00:21:58.770
mismatch."

00:21:59.020 --> 00:22:01.120
Human is dead?

00:22:03.100 --> 00:22:04.140
Someone...

00:22:06.690 --> 00:22:07.720
...died.

00:22:08.305 --> 00:23:08.516
